news.title: Telangana: Incomplete 2BHK units to be put under Indiramma scheme
news.para: The Congress govt has decided to finish the construction of the incomplete 2-BHK units and allot them, along with those completed but lying vacant, in all nearly a lakh 2-BHK units, to eligible landless poor.

news.title: JK Cement to acquire 60% stake in Saifco Cements, to enter Jammu & Kashmir
news.para: The JK Group firm will acquire a 60 per cent stake in Saifco Cements, which has an integrated manufacturing unit at Khunmoh in Srinagar, at a valuation of Rs 174 crore, according to a joint statement.

news.title: Mumbai: Cheating case against Neptune Venture & Developers dropped, EOW files closure report
news.para: This followed a complaint by 55 flat buyers alleging that the company collected substantial sums from buyers, but failed to deliver the promised flats in its ‘100 Above' project in Bhandup West.

news.title: New norms for tilting buildings in West Bengal
news.para: ​If satisfied, the civic body will send the details of the lifting mechanism to a reputed engineering institution for necessary vetting. Permission for the lifting will be granted only after the lifting mechanism plan is vetted.

news.title: Mumbai businessman files FIR alleging Rs 250 crore fraud in real estate investment
news.para: Vira, a construction and finance entrepreneur, has alleged in the FIR that he was deceived into investing ₹150 crore on behalf of his group in the Sunshine Group and was subsequently defrauded through forged documents and unauthorised loans amounting to Rs 250 crore.

news.title: Goa:Land conversion of three lakh sq meter for settlement gets TCP board nod
news.para: Under Section 39A of the TCP Act, the board approved 15 proposals for the conversion of 2.8 lakh sqm of orchards, paddy fields, and no-development slopes.

news.title: Noida authority renews demand for Rs 10,000 crore unused Unitech land
news.para: At a Jan 21 meeting, headed by retired SC judge Abhay Manohar Sapre, adviser to the govt-approved Unitech board of directors, Authority officials emphasised that the amount represents public money, which must be recovered to ensure the completion of urban infrastructure and amenities that benefit residents.

news.title: Haryana amends licensing rules for projects to improve transparency
news.para: As per the old rules, the department first assessed the financial capacity of the builder at the time of issuing the letter of intent (LoI). The financial strength of the builder was examined once again before the issuance of the licence.

news.title: Nirala World buys 2.5 acre land in Greater Noida for Rs 175 crore
news.para: "We recently purchased a land parcel in Greater Noida West through an auction process," said Suresh Garg, Chairman and Managing Director of Nirala World.

news.title: Macrotech Developers' net profit rises 87.02% in Q3 FY25
news.para: Macrotech Developers' net consolidated total income and gains stood at Rs 4,146.6 crore in Q3 FY25, a growth of 40.15 per cent from Rs 2,958.7 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: AT&T secures $850 million from sale-leaseback of real estate to Reign Capital
news.para: Sale-leaseback is a financing option in which a company sells part of its assets to raise capital and leases back the same property to run its operations.

news.title: CEAN writes to collector seeking survey on real estate layouts in the Nilgiris
news.para: "Most of the real estate projects in the district violate section 3 of the TNRERA Act,", Surjit K Chaudhary, chairperson and coordinator of CEAN, alleged.

news.title: Plots can't be auctioned without verifying open space status: Telangana HC
news.para: Justice T Vinod Kumar of gave the order while hearing a petition by KPHB Sri Venkata Ramana Colony Welfare Association (Phase XV). The order will be in force till Jan 30, the next date of hearing.

news.title: Telangana CM seeks central support for housing and metro expansion
news.para: He also sought financial support of Rs 56,139 crore for various projects, including the metro rail phase II expansion, Musi river rejuvenation, and underground drainage networks for GHMC and surrounding towns.

news.title: Haryana government allocates plots under Mukhyamantri Gramin Awas Yojana 2.0
news.para: "The chief minister's vision is that no poor person in Haryana should remain without a roof. The government is continuously making efforts in this direction," an official statement said.

news.title: Odisha government launches survey to select beneficiaries under PM awas yojana
news.para: The survey will continue for about two months. It will include all the eligible families as per the promises made by Prime Minister Narendra Modi to provide 'pucca' houses to all, the minister said.

news.title: Landeed raises $5 million in Series X funding round
news.para: The Hyderabad-based startup stated that this round continues its earlier fundraising, which was among the largest seed rounds by a proptech startup in 2023.

news.title: UltraTech's open offer for India Cements oversubscribed
news.para: The ₹390-per-share offer, open from January 8 to 21, was subscribed 110%. It will increase UltraTech's stake in India Cements to 81.49%.The ₹390-per-share offer, open from January 8 to 21, was subscribed 110%.

news.title: SWAMIH Fund completes 50,000 homes since 2019
news.para: The fund set up in 2019 is managed by SBICAP Ventures Ltd, a State Bank Group company and it has no precedent or comparable peer fund in India or in the global markets.

news.title: ED to probe buyers of Dubai properties for forex violations and money laundering
news.para: The central agency has collated information gathered from its sources with the data received from the Income Tax (I-T) department and the Reserve Bank of India. A probe has begun, official sources told ET.
